    "updated_at": "2015-12-01T18:00:19Z",
    "body": "Interestingly enough, after enabling logging, I get this error message:\nERROR:gpu_video_decode_accelerator.cc(280)] HW video decode not available for profile 1\nas soon as the video starts rendering in the Flash Player.\nNot sure if Chrome would produce the same error and I wouldn't know how I'd go about getting this out of Chromium/Chrome. (Edit : After investigating, it seems Chromium get this error)\n\nThe logs I get in the console look more precisely like so:\n[8416:1201/023656:VERBOSE1:child_thread_impl.cc(343)] Mojo is disabled on child\n[5532:1201/023656:VERBOSE1:child_thread_impl.cc(343)] Mojo is disabled on child\n[5532:1201/023656:ERROR:renderer_main.cc(200)] Running without renderer sandbox\n[6912:1201/023658:VERBOSE1:dhcp_proxy_script_adapter_fetcher_win.cc(262)] Error fetching PAC URL from DHCP: 2\n[6912:1201/023659:VERBOSE1:proxy_service.cc(1236)] Failed configuring with PAC script, falling-back to manual proxy servers.\n[8416:1201/023700:VERBOSE1:gles2_cmd_decoder.cc(2765)] GL_OES_packed_depth_stencil supported.\n[6912:1201/023700:VERBOSE2:ppapi_plugin_process_host.cc(416)] ppapi plugin process launched.\n[7680:1201/023700:VERBOSE1:child_thread_impl.cc(343)] Mojo is disabled on child\nNOT SANDBOXED\nVector smash protection is enabled.\n[8416:1201/023700:VERBOSE1:gles2_cmd_decoder.cc(2765)] GL_OES_packed_depth_stencil supported.\n[6912:1201/023707:VERBOSE1:dhcp_proxy_script_adapter_fetcher_win.cc(262)] Error fetching PAC URL from DHCP: 2\n[8416:1201/023713:ERROR:gpu_video_decode_accelerator.cc(280)] HW video decode not available for profile 1\n[6912:1201/023744:VERBOSE1:dhcp_proxy_script_adapter_fetcher_win.cc(262)] Error fetching PAC URL from DHCP: 2\n[6912:1201/023945:VERBOSE1:dhcp_proxy_script_adapter_fetcher_win.cc(262)] Error fetching PAC URL from DHCP: 2\n[6912:1201/024705:VERBOSE3:cookie_monster.cc(2284)] Time for recording cookie stats (us): 9\n..\n\nIf I go in the chrome://gpu within Electron, I get: \nGraphics Feature Status\nCanvas: Hardware accelerated\nFlash: Hardware accelerated\nFlash Stage3D: Hardware accelerated\nFlash Stage3D Baseline profile: Hardware accelerated\nCompositing: Hardware accelerated\nMultiple Raster Threads: Enabled\nRasterization: Software only. Hardware acceleration disabled\nVideo Decode: Hardware accelerated\nVideo Encode: Hardware accelerated\nWebGL: Hardware accelerated\n\nDriver Bug Workarounds\nclear_uniforms_before_first_program_use\nexit_on_context_lost\nscalarize_vec_and_mat_constructor_args\ntexsubimage_faster_than_teximage\n\nProblems Detected\nSome drivers are unable to reset the D3D device in the GPU process sandbox\nApplied Workarounds: exit_on_context_lost\nTexSubImage is faster for full uploads on ANGLE\nApplied Workarounds: texsubimage_faster_than_teximage\nClear uniforms before first program use on all platforms: 124764, 349137\nApplied Workarounds: clear_uniforms_before_first_program_use\nAlways rewrite vec/mat constructors to be consistent: 398694\nApplied Workarounds: scalarize_vec_and_mat_constructor_args\nAccelerated rasterization has been disabled, either via about:flags or command line.\nDisabled Features: rasterization\n\nWhich seems just the same as within Chrome.\n....\n"
  },
