    "updated_at": "2015-12-01T18:43:09Z",
    "body": "After more investigation. If I disable Hardware Acceleration within the Flash Player Settings (by right-clicking on the Flash element and unchecking the option), the error doesn't appear. In this case, the hardware acceleration is disabled and the GPU/CPU usage of Electron is the same as described above. Thus I conclude that Flash hardware acceleration doesn't seem to work in Electron by default.\nAm I missing some file or a flag that might enable hardware acceleration in Flash ?\n"
  },
