    "updated_at": "2015-12-01T19:20:05Z",
    "body": "Probably related, if I go see a video on youtube that uses HTML5 video (dash, thus h264) I get this error message (while the video still plays, probably in software mode, and this is the HTML 5 Youtube player): \nERROR:gpu_video_decode_accelerator.cc(280)] HW video decode not available for profile 12\n\nSo, I'm guessing this issue doesn't only affect Flash, but also any video decoding that attempts to access hardware acceleration.\n"
